@YaelDillies That ended up needing a few more changes to use the new instances. I was wondering, would an instance of `Fact (0 \le 1)` under `[ZeroLeOneClass \alpha]` be useful? E.g. it would trivialize the `BoundedOrder` instance for `UnitInterval`.

> @YaelDillies That ended up needing a few more changes to use the new instances. I was wondering, would an instance of `Fact (0 \le 1)` under `[ZeroLeOneClass \alpha]` be useful? E.g. it would trivialize the `BoundedOrder` instance for `UnitInterval`.

It is an option, but I would keep that for a separate PR because
1. Global `Fact` instances slow down all `Fact` TC searches
2. `UnitInterval` is kind of considered a concrete type in itself
OK then I'm happy with this PR if you are.
Done.

Can you instead turn the `abbrev`s into instances? Also note `Set.Icc.completeLinearOrder`
Also `Set.Icc.completeLattice`? That's the only place where `Icc.boundedOrder` is used.

```suggestion
    have : Fact (s ‚â§ t) := ‚ü®hsa.trans <| hbt.trans' hab.le‚ü©
```

```suggestion
  have : Fact (a ‚â§ b) := ‚ü®hab‚ü©
```
and everywhere else

```suggestion
instance : BoundedOrder I := have : Fact ((0 : ‚Ñù) ‚â§ 1) := ‚ü®zero_le_one‚ü©; inferInstance
```
